<br /><b><i>St. Boniface, Bishop of Mentz and Martyr</i></b>
<br /><i>“He came from England to Rome, and was sent by Gregory II to Germany to preach the faith of Christ to the people of that country. Having converted large multitudes to the Christian religion, especially in Friesland, he merited the title of Apostle of the Germans. Being finally put to the sword by the furious Gentiles, he consummated his martyrdom with Eobanus and some other servants of God.”</i> (Based on the Roman Martyrology)
