<br /><b>St. Barnabas, Apostle and Martyr</b>
<br /><i>“By the disciples he was ordained apostle of the Gentiles with St. Paul, and with him traversed many regions, fulfilling his commission to preach the Gospel. At length he went to Cyprus, where he ennobled his apostolate by a glorious martyrdom. Through his own revelation his body was found, in the time of the emperor Zeno, together with a copy of St. Matthew's gospel copied with his own hand.”</i> (Based on the Roman Martyrology)
